article.description: — Tyler Tejada scored 18 points as Towson beat Campbell 77-43 on Saturday night.
article.headline: Tejada's 18 help Towson beat Campbell 77-43
article.story: TOWSON, Md. -- — Tyler Tejada scored 18 points as Towson beat Campbell 77-43 on Saturday night. Tejada also contributed six rebounds for the Tigers (11-8, 4-2 Coastal Athletic Association). Nendah Tarke scored 12 points, going 5 of 10 (2 for 5 from 3-point range). Christian May shot 3 for 9, including 3 for 7 from beyond the arc to finish with 11 points. Anthony Dell'Orso led the Fighting Camels (9-10, 3-3) in scoring, finishing with 15 points and three steals. Campbell also got 14 points from Gediminas Mokseckas. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
